Hospital Management System

A web application that streamlines hospital operations by managing patients, doctors, appointments, and related records digitally. It helps improve efficiency and reduce manual work for administrators, doctors and patients.

ğŸ§± Features

User roles: Admin, Doctor, Patient

Admin dashboard: Manage users, doctors, patients, appointments

Doctor dashboard: View upcoming appointments, view patient history

Patient view: Browse & search doctors by name or department, Book appointments

Database models for Users, Departments, Appointments, Treatments, DoctorAvailability

Secure password hashing using werkzeug.security

Timestamps stored in UTC for consistency

ğŸ›  Technology & Stack

Python 3.x

Flask (Web framework)

Flaskâ€‘SQLAlchemy (ORM)

SQL database (e.g., SQLite, PostgreSQL)

HTML templates for front end (with Flask render_template)

Password hashing via werkzeug.security.generate_password_hash / check_password_hash

ğŸ“ Project Structure
/instance/             # Config files, environment variables  
/templates/            # HTML template files  
app.py                 # Main Flask application  
models.py              # ORM models for Users, Departments, Appointments, Treatments, DoctorAvailability  
requirements.txt       # Python dependencies  

ğŸ”§ Getting Started
Prerequisites

Python 3.x installed

Virtual environment recommended

Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/24f1001665/hospital-management-system.git
cd hospital-management-system



Create and activate a virtual environment:

python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate


Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt


Initialize the database (example):

python app.py   # The `init_db()` call will create tables

Start the server:

python app.py

Open your browser at http://localhost:5000

âœ… Usage / Workflow

Admin logs in â†’ can add/edit doctors & departments

Patient logs in â†’ browses doctors (by name or department) â†’ books an appointment

Doctor logs in â†’ sees upcoming appointments (next 7 days) â†’ clicks patient â†’ views their appointment history & treatments

ğŸ›¡ Security & Best Practices

Passwords are stored hashed (never plain text)

Timestamps stored in UTC (datetime.utcnow())

Use @role_required(...) decorators to enforce role-based access

Important: For production, set FLASK_DEBUG=False and use a production-ready web server

Use environment variables (not hard-coded) for secret keys, database URLs
